events.title: How many jobs added in December?
events.description:
This market will resolve according to the nonfarm payroll employment reported by the BLS "Employment Situation Summary" for December 2025, scheduled to be released on January 9, 2026, 8:30 AM ET.

If the reported value falls exactly between two brackets, then this market will resolve to the higher range bracket.

If no data for December is released by the date the next month's data is scheduled to be released, this market will resolve based on data from the last available month.

The BLS "Employment Situation Summary" may be found here: https://www.bls.gov/bls/newsrels.htm

events.title: How many jobs added in December?
events.description: This is a negrisk market group over how many nonfarm payroll jobs the US will add in December 2024 according to the BLS.

markets.question: Will US add between 100k and 150k jobs in December 2024?
markets.description:
Total nonfarm payroll employment rose by 227,000 in November 2024.

This market will resolve to "Yes" if the United States gains between 100,000 (inclusive) and 150,000 (exclusive) in nonfarm payroll employment according to the BLS "Employment Situation Summary" for November, scheduled to be released on January 10, 2025, 8:30 AM ET. Otherwise, this market will resolve to "No".

The BLS "Employment Situation Summary" may be found here: https://www.bls.gov/bls/newsrels.htm
